<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="124" pageId="4" pageNumber="123" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1958,2019]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="124" pageId="4" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,259,1958,1983]" pageId="4" pageNumber="123">Remarks</emphasis>
. The species of 
<taxonomicName box="[458,512,1959,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Arge" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[458,512,1959,1982]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="123">Arge</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distributed in all biogeographical regions, except the 
<collectingCountry box="[1194,1302,1958,1983]" name="Antarctica" pageId="4" pageNumber="123">Antarctic</collectingCountry>
. The genus comprises 
<number box="[273,314,1995,2019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="123" value="113.0">113</number>
valid species for the Afrotropical Region (
<bibRefCitation author="Taeger" box="[804,1016,1994,2019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="123" refString="Taeger, A., Blank, S. M. &amp; Liston, A. D. (2010) World catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera). Zootaxa, 2580, 1 - 1064." type="journal article" year="2010">
Taeger 
<emphasis box="[890,948,1994,2019]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="123">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[956,1016,1995,2019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="123" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and is the most species-rich sawfly genus of this region. This list by 
<bibRefCitation box="[533,760,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" refString="Taeger, A., Blank, S. M. &amp; Liston, A. D. (2010) World catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera). Zootaxa, 2580, 1 - 1064." type="journal article">
Taeger 
<emphasis box="[618,677,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[693,752,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
is mainly based on the revisions by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pasteels" box="[1183,1350,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" refString="Pasteels, J. (1953) Prodromes d'une faune des Tenthredinoidea (Hymenoptera) de l'Afrique noire. I. Argidae. Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 23, 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="1953">Pasteels (1953</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pasteels" box="[1364,1423,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" refString="Pasteels, J. (1963) Prodrome d'une faune des Tenthredinoidea de l'Afrique noire. IV. 2 e supplement aux Argidae. Bulletin et Annales de la Societe Royale d'Entomologie de Belgique, 99, 540 - 560." type="journal article" year="1963">1963</bibRefCitation>
), who especially concentrated on the fauna of the 
<collectingCountry box="[706,876,188,213]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Belgian Congo</collectingCountry>
and the eastern, adjacent countries (
<emphasis box="[1294,1329,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">i.e.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[1337,1431,188,213]" name="Rwanda" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,243,223,248]" name="Uganda" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Uganda</collectingCountry>
). Later 
<number box="[334,362,224,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="18.0">18</number>
species were described, and four species synonymized (
<bibRefCitation author="Koch" box="[1018,1288,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" refString="Koch, F. &amp; Goergen, G. (2010) Eight new species of Arge from South Africa and Namibia (Hymenoptera: Symphyta: Argidae). Lambillionea, 110 (1), 19 - 34." type="journal article" year="2010">
Koch &amp; Goergen 
<number box="[1228,1288,224,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Koch 
<number box="[1373,1431,224,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="2011.0">2011</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Koch" box="[151,400,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" refString="Koch, F. &amp; Eardley, C. D. (2011) Revision of the Afrotropical Arge mirabilipes group, with description of two new species and annotations to other Arge species of this region (Hymenoptera: Symphyta: Argidae: Arginae). African Invertebrates, 52 (2), 457 - 470. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5733 / afin. 052.0213" type="journal article" year="2011">
Koch &amp; Eardley 
<number box="[342,400,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Koch 
<number box="[479,539,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="2012.0">2012</number>
a; 
<bibRefCitation author="Koch" box="[563,809,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" refString="Koch, F. &amp; Liston, A. D. (2012 a) Notes on Afrotropical sawflies of the genus Arge Schrank, 1802, with the description of a new species (Hymenoptera: Symphyta, Argidae). Entomologische Zeitschrift, 122 (4), 177 - 181." type="journal article" year="2012" yearSuffix="a">
Koch &amp; Liston 
<number box="[738,797,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="2012.0">2012</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
, b; 
<bibRefCitation author="Koch" box="[850,977,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" refString="Koch, F. (2013) A contribution to Arge (Schrank, 1802) of South Africa, with description of a new species Hymenoptera: Symphyta, Argidae). Entomologische Zeitschrift, 123 (1), 23 - 31." type="journal article" year="2013">
Koch 
<number box="[917,977,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), thus leading to 
<number box="[1169,1211,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="127.0">127</number>
recognized species. Nevertheless, the taxonomy of the Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[710,764,296,319]" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Arge" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[710,764,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Arge</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species is partly outdated, incomplete and in some cases incorrect, rendering a revision necessary. So far only the 
<taxonomicName box="[787,944,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Arge" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis box="[787,944,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Arge capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group that is distributed in southern Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Koch" box="[239,494,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" refString="Koch, F. &amp; Liston, A. D. (2012 b) On the Arge capensis species group, with descriptions of four new species (Hymenoptera: Symphyta, Argidae). Entomologische Zeitschrift, 122 (6), 261 - 268." type="journal article" year="2012" yearSuffix="b">
Koch &amp; Liston 
<number box="[422,480,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="2012.0">2012</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
) and the 
<taxonomicName box="[603,794,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Arge" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilipes">
<emphasis box="[603,794,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Arge mirabilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (
<bibRefCitation author="Koch" box="[974,1231,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" refString="Koch, F. &amp; Eardley, C. D. (2011) Revision of the Afrotropical Arge mirabilipes group, with description of two new species and annotations to other Arge species of this region (Hymenoptera: Symphyta: Argidae: Arginae). African Invertebrates, 52 (2), 457 - 470. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5733 / afin. 052.0213" type="journal article" year="2011">
Koch &amp; Eardley 
<number box="[1173,1231,368,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Koch 
<number box="[1315,1373,368,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" value="2012.0">2012</number>
a) are defined and revised.
</paragraph>
